56#ifdef _MSC_VER
57/*
58 * Under MSVC, functions exported by a loadable module must be marked
59 * "dllexport". Other compilers don't need that.
60 * Borrowed from PostgreSQL file win32.h
61 */
62#define PGDLLEXPORT __declspec (dllexport)
63/*
64 * Avoids warning C4996: 'strdup': The POSIX name for this item is deprecated.
65 */
66#define strdup _strdup
67#endif

76#define DOUBLE_PAD(size) ( (size) + ((size) % 8 ? (8 - (size) % 8) : 0 ) )
77
81typedef struct
82{
83 int32 vl_len_;
84 uint8 settype;
85 uint8 basetype;
86 int16 flags;
87 int32 count;
88 int32 maxcount;
89 int16 bboxsize;
90} Set;
91
95typedef struct
96{
97 uint8 spantype;
98 uint8 basetype;
99 bool lower_inc;
100 bool upper_inc;
101 char padding[4];
102 Datum lower;
103 Datum upper;
104} Span;
105
109typedef struct
110{
111 int32 vl_len_;
112 uint8 spansettype;
113 uint8 spantype;
114 uint8 basetype;
115 char padding;
116 int32 count;
117 int32 maxcount;
118 Span span;
119 Span elems[1];
120} SpanSet;
121
125typedef struct
126{
127 Span period;
128 Span span;
129 int16 flags;
130} TBox;
131
135typedef struct
136{
137 Span period;
138 double xmin;
139 double ymin;
140 double zmin;
141 double xmax;
142 double ymax;
143 double zmax;
144 int32 srid;
145 int16 flags;
146} STBox;
147
151typedef enum

153 ANYTEMPSUBTYPE = 0,
154 TINSTANT = 1,
155 TSEQUENCE = 2,
156 TSEQUENCESET = 3,
157} tempSubtype;

163{
164 INTERP_NONE = 0,
165 DISCRETE = 1,
166 STEP = 2,
167 LINEAR = 3,
168} interpType;
169
174typedef enum
175{
176 INTERSECTS = 0,
177 CONTAINS = 1,
178 TOUCHES = 2,
179 COVERS = 3,
180} spatialRel;

186typedef struct
187{
188 int32 vl_len_;
189 uint8 temptype;
190 uint8 subtype;
191 int16 flags;
192 /* variable-length data follows */
193} Temporal;
194
198typedef struct
199{
200 int32 vl_len_;
201 uint8 temptype;
202 uint8 subtype;
203 int16 flags;
204 TimestampTz t;
205 Datum value;
209 /* variable-length data follows */
210} TInstant;
211
215typedef struct
216{
217 int32 vl_len_;
218 uint8 temptype;
219 uint8 subtype;
220 int16 flags;
221 int32 count;
222 int32 maxcount;
223 int16 bboxsize;
224 char padding[6];
225 Span period;
229 /* variable-length data follows */
230} TSequence;
231
232#define TSEQUENCE_BBOX_PTR(seq) ((void *)(&(seq)->period))
233
237typedef struct
238{
239 int32 vl_len_;
240 uint8 temptype;
241 uint8 subtype;
242 int16 flags;
243 int32 count;
244 int32 totalcount;
246 int32 maxcount;
247 int16 bboxsize;
248 int16 padding;
249 Span period;
253 /* variable-length data follows */
254} TSequenceSet;
255
256#define TSEQUENCESET_BBOX_PTR(ss) ((void *)(&(ss)->period))

305/*****************************************************************************
306 * Error codes
307 *****************************************************************************/
308
309typedef enum
310{
311 MEOS_SUCCESS = 0, // Successful operation
312
313 MEOS_ERR_INTERNAL_ERROR = 1, // Unspecified internal error
314 MEOS_ERR_INTERNAL_TYPE_ERROR = 2, // Internal type error
315 MEOS_ERR_VALUE_OUT_OF_RANGE = 3, // Internal out of range error
316 MEOS_ERR_DIVISION_BY_ZERO = 4, // Internal division by zero error
317 MEOS_ERR_MEMORY_ALLOC_ERROR = 5, // Internal malloc error
318 MEOS_ERR_AGGREGATION_ERROR = 6, // Internal aggregation error
319 MEOS_ERR_DIRECTORY_ERROR = 7, // Internal directory error
320 MEOS_ERR_FILE_ERROR = 8, // Internal file error
321
322 MEOS_ERR_INVALID_ARG = 10, // Invalid argument
323 MEOS_ERR_INVALID_ARG_TYPE = 11, // Invalid argument type
324 MEOS_ERR_INVALID_ARG_VALUE = 12, // Invalid argument value
325
326 MEOS_ERR_MFJSON_INPUT = 20, // MFJSON input error
327 MEOS_ERR_MFJSON_OUTPUT = 21, // MFJSON output error
328 MEOS_ERR_TEXT_INPUT = 22, // Text input error
329 MEOS_ERR_TEXT_OUTPUT = 23, // Text output error
330 MEOS_ERR_WKB_INPUT = 24, // WKB input error
331 MEOS_ERR_WKB_OUTPUT = 25, // WKB output error
332 MEOS_ERR_GEOJSON_INPUT = 26, // GEOJSON input error
333 MEOS_ERR_GEOJSON_OUTPUT = 27, // GEOJSON output error
334
335} errorCode;
